\begin_layout Plain Layout
Differentialform
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{aufgabe}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Prüfen Sie, ob die Differentialform 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega(x)=(2x_{1}-x_{2})x_{3}\,\D x_{1}-x_{1}x_{3}\,\D x_{2}+x_{1}(x_{1}-x_{2})\,\D x_{3}
\]

\end_inset

exakt ist.
 Berechnen Sie ggf.
 das zugehörige Potential.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{aufgabe}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Flüsse von Vektorfeldern
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{aufgabe}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "aufgabe-gr-fluss-roboter"

\end_inset

Zu dem Vektorfeld 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(x)=\sin(x_{3})\frac{\partial}{\partial x_{1}}+\cos x_{3}\frac{\partial}{\partial x_{2}}
\]

\end_inset

des mobilen Roboters bestimme man den Fluss 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 Geben Sie dazu einen frei wählbaren Anfangswert 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in\R^{3}$
\end_inset

 vor.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{aufgabe}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{aufgabe}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Zu dem Vektorfeld
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 aus Aufgabe
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "aufgabe-gr-fluss-roboter"

\end_inset

 löse man die matrixwertige Variationsgleichung
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Variationsgleichung"

\end_inset

 sowie die adjungierte Variationsgleichung
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:AdjVariationsgleichung"

\end_inset

.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{aufgabe}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Lösungen
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Lösungen}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Die Basisdarstellung lautet
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(x)=\left(a_{11}x_{1}+a_{12}x_{2}\right)\frac{\partial}{\partial x_{1}}+\left(a_{21}x_{1}+a_{22}x_{2}\right)\frac{\partial}{\partial x_{1}}.
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset

In Gl.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Ableitung-SF-VF"

\end_inset

 betrachtet man die Ableitung des mit dem Skalarfeld
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 skalierten Vektorfeldes
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

.
 Die Ableitung des 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

-ten Elements nach
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $x_{j}$
\end_inset

 ergibt sich aus der Produktregel: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial\left(h(x)f_{i}(x)\right)}{\partial x_{j}}=\frac{\partial h(x)}{\partial x_{j}}f_{i}(x)+h(x)\frac{\partial f_{i}(x)}{\partial x_{j}}.
\]

\end_inset

 Diese elementweise berechnete Ableitung lässt sich mit 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial\left(h(x)f(x)\right)}{\partial x}=f(x)\,h^{\prime}(x)+h(x)\,f^{\prime}(x)
\]

\end_inset

in Matrix-Notation angeben.
 Gl.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Ableitung-VF-VF"

\end_inset

 und
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Ableitung-Skalarprodukt"

\end_inset

 lassen sich in ähnlicher Weise verifizieren.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Die Differentialform ist wegen 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{rcccl}
\frac{\partial\omega_{1}}{\partial x_{2}} & = & -x_{3} & = & \frac{\partial\omega_{2}}{\partial x_{1}}\\
\frac{\partial\omega_{1}}{\partial x_{3}} & = & 2x_{1}-x_{2} & = & \frac{\partial\omega_{3}}{\partial x_{1}}\\
\frac{\partial\omega_{2}}{\partial x_{3}} & = & -x_{1} & = & \frac{\partial\omega_{3}}{\partial x_{2}}
\end{array}
\]

\end_inset

geschlossen.
 Nach dem Poincaréschen Lemma (Lemma
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "lem:poincare"

\end_inset

) ist sie dann auch exakt.
 Das Potential 
\begin_inset Formula $h(x)=(x_{1}-x_{2})x_{1}x_{3}$
\end_inset

 erhält man durch Integration entsprechend Gl.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:potential-poincare"

\end_inset

.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Das Vektorfeld
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 kann der nicht\SpecialChar softhyphen
linearen Differentialgleichung 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{x}=f(x)$
\end_inset

 zugeordnet werden.
 Zusammen mit der Anfangsbedingung 
\begin_inset Formula $x(0)=p$
\end_inset

 erhält man die Anfangswertaufgabe
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{lcllcl}
\dot{x}_{1} & = & \sin x_{3},\quad & x_{1}(0) & = & p_{1},\\
\dot{x}_{2} & = & \cos x_{3},\quad & x_{2}(0) & = & p_{2},\\
\dot{x}_{3} & = & 0,\quad & x_{3}(0) & = & p_{3}.
\end{array}
\]

\end_inset

Die letzte Differentialgleichung hat die konstante Lösung 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{3}(t)\equiv p_{3}$
\end_inset

.
 Dadurch haben die ersten zwei Differentialgleichungen eine konstante rechte
 Seite und somit die Lösungen 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
x_{1}(t) & = & p_{1}+t\sin p_{3},\\
x_{2}(t) & = & p_{2}+t\cos p_{3}.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Insgesamt erhält man damit den Fluss 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\varphi_{t}(p)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
p_{1}+t\sin p_{3}\\
p_{2}+t\cos p_{3}\\
p_{3}
\end{array}\right).\label{eq:gr-roboter-fluss-f}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset

Die Lösung der matrixwertigen Variationsgleichung
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Variationsgleichung"

\end_inset

 erhält man entsprechend Prop.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pro:Variationsgleichung"

\end_inset

 aus der Ableitung des dem Vektorfeld
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 zugehörigen Flusses
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:gr-roboter-fluss-f"

\end_inset

 nach dem Anfangswert:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
X(t)=\varphi_{t}^{\prime}(p)=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & \phantom{-}t\cos p_{3}\\
0 & 1 & -t\sin p_{3}\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right).\label{eq:loes-gr-Var-X}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Die Lösung
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Loesung_Adj_Variationsgl"

\end_inset

 der adjungierten Variationsgleichung
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:AdjVariationsgleichung"

\end_inset

 erhält man entsprechend Gl.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Loesung_adj_als_Inverse"

\end_inset

 aus der Inversen von
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:loes-gr-Var-X"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(t)=X^{-1}(t)=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & -t\cos p_{3}\\
0 & 1 & \phantom{-}t\sin p_{3}\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right).
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{loesung}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

